The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning and human feedback to train intelligent agents, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The modifications made to the COACH algorithm involve the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of real-time human feedback to train the agent also involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the application of the algorithm in the 3D world of Minecraft suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
